The Apthorp, 1908. Designed by Clinton & Russell and built by William Waldorf Astor, who named it after the Apthorp Farm, of which the site used to be part. The Apthorp is a New York City designated landmark and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.

I bought this painted cabinet up in Connecticut in the late aughts and it was in my last three apartments (swipe to see the first). What I learned from living with this piece for 12+ years is that I like objects and tchotchkes but I like them behind glass. It keeps it all tidier. And dust free. He didn’t make it to my new place but I couldn’t part with him so he’s on extended sabbatical with an ex in New Orleans. 

📷 @petermurdock_photo

Thank you @archdigest for sharing this family home we created for such amazing clients and their two young daughters. We rethought almost every detail - a reconfigured floorplan with the addition of a powder room, a new kitchen, three baths, custom millwork throughout and a new trim package. We did keep the original floors and fireplace in this Emery Roth building from 1916! Swipe to see the entry before. Thank you Team AD @amyastley @alevasseur1 @samuelcochran @madeleineluckel @michaelsshome @melissahmaria and to the lovely story by @whatpaolasees and last but not least @analisabixler for helping me knock it outta the park! 💥
